From 2222222222222222222222222222222222222222 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Apr 2026 16:05:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] driver: declare get_driver_common_interfaces

The core driver calls get_driver_common_interfaces() but no prototype is
visible in this tree, which causes an implicit declaration build error
with the kernel toolchain.

Declare the external symbol with the expected pointer return type so the
module compiles cleanly.
---
 driver/include/txx-funcs.h | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/driver/include/txx-funcs.h b/driver/include/txx-funcs.h
index 6f6ef8c..4f9078a 100644
--- a/driver/include/txx-funcs.h
+++ b/driver/include/txx-funcs.h
@@ -331,6 +331,7 @@ struct net *private_get_init_net(void);
 /* isp driver interface */
 void private_get_isp_priv_mem(unsigned int *phyaddr, unsigned int *size);
 
+struct jz_driver_common_interfaces *get_driver_common_interfaces(void);
 int private_driver_get_interface(void);
 
 #endif /*__TXX_DRV_FUNCS_H__*/
-- 
2.49.0

